ZH: 他是一个外行，对这个领域一窍不通。
EN: He is a layman and knows nothing about this field.

ZH: 她虽然是个外行，但愿意学习新知识。
EN: Although she is a layman, she is willing to learn new knowledge.

ZH: 这个问题太专业了，我是个外行，不懂。
EN: This problem is too professional, I am a layman and do not understand.

ZH: 作为一个外行，他很少发表自己的意见。
EN: As a layman, he rarely expresses his own opinions.

ZH: 我是个外行，你可以向更专业的人请教。
EN: I am a layman, you can ask for advice from more professional people.

ZH: 小明虽然是个外行，但他对这方面很感兴趣。
EN: Although Xiaoming is a layman, he is very interested in this aspect.

ZH: 她接受了外行的建议，改进了自己的作品。
EN: She accepted the layman's advice and improved her work.

ZH: 他对这个技术领域是个外行，需要不断学习。
EN: He is a layman in this technical field and needs to keep learning.

ZH: 她从外行变成了专家，经过长时间的学习和实践。
EN: She has transformed from a layman to an expert after a long period of study and practice.

ZH: 虽然是外行，但他能够快速适应新的环境。
EN: Although he is a layman, he can quickly adapt to a new environment.

ZH: 他是行家中的一员，而不是外行。
EN: He is a member of the experts, not a layman.

ZH: 在这个领域，他一直是个外行，需要更多实践。
EN: He has always been a layman in this field and needs more practice.

ZH: 老师从外行的角度给予学生指导和启发。
EN: The teacher gives guidance and inspiration to students from the perspective of a layman.

ZH: 孩子们对这个问题比外行更有深入的了解。
EN: Children have a deeper understanding of this issue than laymen.

ZH: 写作对他来说是个外行，需要不断学习和锻炼。
EN: Writing is a layman for him, and he needs to keep learning and practicing.

ZH: 这个外行对音乐的欣赏能力非常有限。
EN: This layman has very limited ability to appreciate music.

ZH: 他把外行的见解融入到了自己的作品中。
EN: He incorporates the layman's insights into his own work.

ZH: 对于外行来说，这个问题可能有点难以理解。
EN: For a layman, this issue may be a bit difficult to understand.

ZH: 她是个外行，但是对于新事物充满好奇心。
EN: She is a layman, but she is curious about new things.

ZH: 让一个外行来解释这个问题，可能会引起误解。
EN: Letting a layman explain this issue may cause misunderstanding.
